    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Streamlit is built for GPUs. </strong>Streamlit allows direct access to machine-level primitives like TensorFlow and PyTorch and complements these libraries. For example in this demo, Streamlit’s cache stores the entire <a href="https://research.nvidia.com/publication/2017-10_Progressive-Growing-of" target="_self">NVIDIA celebrity face GAN</a> [2]. This approach enables nearly instantaneous inference as the user updates sliders.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
